<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06155g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06155g">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06155g"> 155(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Comm. Tables / 4 &mdash; 6</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[from Part Three. Christian Duty. The ten Commandments]</font> They are numbered as Ten when they were first delivered to the Jews, but how many were written on each Table is uncertain. The Church Catechism divides them thus&mdash;<mark>Four</mark> on the First Table, teaching our Duty towards God; <mark>Six</mark> on the Second Table, teaching our Duty towards our Neighbour. <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 31-2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
